# Removed Feature Hard-Cut (Mandatory)

- When removing or replacing a feature/config, delete its related code, types, APIs, docs, tests, persisted fields, menu items, and i18n entries in the same change.
- Do not keep legacy UI flows, dead handlers, deprecated state fields, compatibility branches, redundant aliases, or historical fallback paths unless compatibility is explicitly required.
- If compatibility is required, document the scope, cleanup trigger, and removal plan in the same change.
- Keep token/schema renames clean: remove deprecated alias fields after call sites are migrated.
- Prefer clear deletion over commented-out code.

## Example

```text
BAD: Remove a setting from UI but keep backend payload aliases, stale docs, and dead fallback branches.
GOOD: Remove the setting and clean its frontend/backend code, schema fields, docs, and tests together.
```
